{
  "page": "Alton Beesbury",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> Alton Beesbury's canon status is currently unclear. Alton was mentioned in <i>The Official Game of Thrones Cookbook</i>, a book approved by <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> and containing a foreword from Martin himself. Until further information comes out, Alton Beesbury should be considered as a semi-canon character.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Alton_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Alton-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Beesbury\" title=\"House Beesbury\"><img alt=\"House Beesbury.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f5/House_Beesbury.svg/50px-House_Beesbury.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f5/House_Beesbury.svg/75px-House_Beesbury.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f5/House_Beesbury.svg/100px-House_Beesbury.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Maester</span><br />Alton</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\"><img alt=\"Maester.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/50px-Maester.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/75px-Maester.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/100px-Maester.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nAlton Beesbury</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">Maester</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Beesbury\" title=\"House Beesbury\">House Beesbury</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Ben_Beesbury\" title=\"Ben Beesbury\">Ben Beesbury</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Official_Game_of_Thrones_Cookbook&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"The Official Game of Thrones Cookbook (page does not exist)\">The Official Game of Thrones Cookbook</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Alton</b>, born <b>Alton Beesbury</b>, is a <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a> hailing from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Beesbury\" title=\"House Beesbury\">House Beesbury</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Alton_Beesbury&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>According to semi-canon sources, Alton was the only son of <a href=\"/index.php/Ben_Beesbury\" title=\"Ben Beesbury\">Ben Beesbury</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Honeyholt\" title=\"Lord of Honeyholt\">Lord of Honeyholt</a>. Alton joined the <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a> to become a <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a> and renounced his inheritance despite his father's protests. Upon Ben's death, he was succeeded by Alton's cousin, <a href=\"/index.php/Warryn_Beesbury\" title=\"Warryn Beesbury\">Warryn Beesbury</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Alton_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Alton-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Alton_Beesbury&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em; height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em; height:1em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black;\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></